Turkey imports power from Bulgaria , Georgia , Iran . Turkey began importing power from neighbouring Bulgaria , Georgia and Iran to make up the shortfall this year , Energy Minister Recai Kutan said on Thursday . " With the imports of 2 . 5 billion kilowatt hours ( kWh ) , there will not be any shortage in 1997 , " Kutan told a conference . He said Turkey ' s 1997 electricity demand was estimated at 106 billion kWh against its projected output of 104 billion . Electric power production stood at 95 . 4 billion kWh last year when Turkey imported power from Bulgaria and Iran to meet its total consumption of 97 . 5 billion kWh . 
